title: MikroTik BGP
agents: mikrotik
catalog: hw/network/mikrotik
license: GPL
distribution: check_mk
description:
 BGP sessions of a MikroTik Device

 Check is {OK} if a BGP session is established, {WARN} if disabled
 and {CRIT} in any other case.

 To connect to the MikroTik device a special datasource program is
 used (SNMP won't report this information): {MikroTik RouterOS} in 
 Setup > Agents> Other integrations > Hardware

item:
 The BGP session name.

perfdata:
 None

inventory:
 One service per BGP session of the device.
